chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have dementia.
chunks.plain_content:
Dementia and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have dementia.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:

heading_context: Car, motorcycle, bus, coach or lorry licence
chunks.html_content: Fill in form CG1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
